3. Uncertainty in Estimation¶

In [24]:
%matplotlib inline
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
In [25]:
sampleSizeRange = np.linspace(100, 200, 40) # create an array with 40 elements evenly spaced starting from 100 ending at 200
plotVar = np.zeros(len(sampleSizeRange)) # create an array with 40 zeros

for sSize in range(len(sampleSizeRange)):
  numSamples = np.int64(sampleSizeRange[sSize])
  MaxTrial=2000
  vStrial=np.zeros(MaxTrial)
  
  for trial in range(MaxTrial):
    xx = np.random.randn(numSamples,1)
    vStrial[trial] = np.var(xx)

  plotVar[sSize] = np.var(vStrial)

plt.xlabel('Sample Size')
plt.ylabel('Variance')
plt.grid(True)
plt.title('Variance in Estimating the Variance')
plt.plot(sampleSizeRange, plotVar) # plot the graph

4. Bivariate Gaussian Distribution¶

In [26]:
%matplotlib inline
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
In [27]:
#  functions to help us calculate and plot contours on a multivariate Gaussian density
def gauss2D(x, m, C):
  Ci = np.linalg.inv(C)
  dC = np.linalg.det(Ci)
  num = np.exp(-0.5 * np.dot((x-m).T, np.dot(Ci, (x-m))))
  den = 2 * np.pi * dC
  return num/den

def twoDGaussianPlot (nx, ny, m, C):
  x = np.linspace(-5, 5, nx)
  y = np.linspace(-5, 5, ny)
  X, Y = np.meshgrid(x, y, indexing='ij')

  Z = np.zeros([nx, ny])
  for i in range(nx):
    for j in range(ny):
      xvec = np.array([X[i,j], Y[i,j]])
      Z[i,j] = gauss2D(xvec, m, C)
  return X, Y, Z

# plot these using different values of means and covariance matrices
nx, ny = 50, 40
plt.figure(figsize=(6,6))
# first bivariate Gaussian density
m1 = np.array([0, 2])
C1 = np.array([[2, 1], [1,2]], np.float32)
Xp, Yp, Zp = twoDGaussianPlot(nx, ny, m1, C1)
# second bivariate Gaussian density
m2 = np.array([2, 0])
C2 = np.array([[2, -1], [-1,2]], np.float32)
Xp2, Yp2, Zp2 = twoDGaussianPlot(nx, ny, m2, C2)
# third bivariate Gaussian density
m3 = np.array([-2, -2])
C3 = np.array([[2, 0], [0,2]], np.float32)
Xp3, Yp3, Zp3 = twoDGaussianPlot(nx, ny, m3, C3)

plt.contour(Xp, Yp, Zp, 3, )
plt.contour(Xp2, Yp2, Zp2, 3,  )
plt.contour(Xp3, Yp3, Zp3, 3, )
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

In [35]:
# Plot how this projected variance changes as a function of :
nPoints = 50;
pVars = np.zeros(nPoints)
thRange = np.linspace(0, 2*np.pi, nPoints)

for n in range(nPoints):
  theta = thRange[n]
  u = [np.sin(theta), np.cos(theta)]
  pVars[n] = np.var( Y @ u )

plt.plot(pVars)
plt.grid(True)
plt.xlabel("Direction", fontsize=14)
plt.ylabel("Variance of Projections", fontsize=14)
plt.savefig("variance_of_projections.png", dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight')
